Create a session with the File Server to search the file system for
available resource files.  RFs fileServerSession;
CleanupClosePushL(fileServerSession);
User::LeaveIfError(fileServerSession.Connect());

Construct a buffer to save a resource file name. The buffer takes
the neutral-language resource file name as a input parameter to BaflUtils::NearestLanguageFileV2().
It will be updated with a new value after the call.  TBuf<256> filename;
filename.Copy(KRscFilename);
